WORKING WITH DATABASE

A database is any file or file system that you can
- store your data
- manipulate data
- search for a desired item

- Flat files (text or binary)
- Flat file systems
- Non-relational databases (eg. MongoDB)
- Relational databases (eg. MySQL)

Relational Database Systems (RDBMS):
Ease your tasks for quickly inserting, updating, querying, 
deleting the data you have on your hands using SQL.
 - MySQL
 - SQL Server
 - Oracle
 - PostgreSQL
- Stores the data in tables and relations between those tables.

Open MySQL Workbench
	table is a data type (eg. Customer)
	row is a single instance of (eg. customer)
 